{
  "stem": "21308.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can only say through my own eyes, we would have fought anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I knew that we-- we weren't fit to go to war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- I mean, I just know that to be true.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we thought that we got grace.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, we did get grace.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We got grace for a year.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when people say, why didn't the British do more, I don't see that they could have done anymore because no money had been spent on the Army.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That is why we were still on two shillings a day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were only volunteers, there were no-- there was no conscription.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In fact, conscription didn't come in until we had the militia scheme in I think it was May 1939.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --everybody hoped and prayed that it would-- it wouldn't go any farther.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But of course, we now know that he never intended stopping.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Although Great Britain was one of the great powers, she had virtually divested herself of her armed force.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Navy was there, but the Air Force had to be totally re-equipped.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in fact, I remember seeing the first Hurricanes flying.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So no, I think that at that time, they-- there was no alternative to it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because the French were no good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And of course, the French were the major military power.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But they weren't any good anymore than they were in 1940.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They went into the bag in the millions in 1940 instead of 1938.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The war broke out on the 3rd of September '39 and I was in France a week later with my regiment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We sailed to Saint-Nazaire on the west coast on the Loire River, the mouth of the River Loire.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
